Implemented:
- Added env/config-based realtime permission gate:
  - `MACHINING_MONITOR_ALLOW_REALTIME=1` enables realtime tab/features.
  - Safe default denies realtime access unless explicitly granted.
  - `MACHINING_MONITOR_ROLE` fallback supports role defaults (`web`/`limited` => utilization-only, `admin`/`full` => realtime allowed when explicit flag is not set).
- `app.py` now resolves realtime permission and passes it to `RuntimeInfoDialog` without changing existing CLI args.
- `RuntimeInfoDialog` now:
  - exposes `is_realtime_access_enabled()`,
  - removes realtime UI when permission is denied,
  - blocks full PLC snapshot escalation and runtime mapping payload when realtime is denied.
- `MonitorServerController` now mirrors the same permission boundary and skips realtime scan/profile fallback logic in limited mode.

